# Disconnection phases to execute (space-separated list).
#
# Phases are executed in order during VPN disconnection. Typically
# the reverse of PHASES_CONNECT to cleanly undo connection setup.
#
# Built-in phases:
#   dns      - Restore original DNS configuration
#   vpn      - Bring down VPN interface (protocol-specific)
#   firewall - Clean up packet filter (PF) tables
#
# The order matters! DNS should be restored before VPN teardown,
# and firewall cleanup should happen last.
#
# Phase resolution follows same rules as PHASES_CONNECT but uses
# "_down" suffix instead of "_up" suffix.
#
# Example custom phase for disconnect:
#   ${VPN_SWITCH_BASE}/.include/phase/custom_routing_down.sh
#
# Usage:
#   - Phases execute in specified order
#   - Each phase outputs shell commands for disconnect.sh
#   - Customize by editing .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_PHASES_DISCONNECT
